    <text>
        <body>

            <pb n="1"/>

            <p rend="right"><placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>April 20. 1853.</date></p>
            <p>My dear Sir&#58;&#8211;</p>

            <p rend="indent(1)">A Committee of the Greene St.<lb/> Congregation Bnai Jeshurun has been appointed
                to<lb/> publish a full and correct statement concerning the<lb/> intentions of the
                Trustees in reference to this to <add>&#63;</add><lb/>
                <add>&#63;</add> in 32<add>&#63;</add> to which subject an undue importance<lb/> has
                been given by the naturally violent&#8211;temperament of<lb/><persName> Mr. John J.
                    Hart</persName> and as I think by the prejudiced<lb/> course adopted by the
                editor of the Asmonean.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The committee&#8212;for which I have the<lb/> honor to be chairman&#8212;have decided
                to make an<lb/> application to you to publish our statement in the<lb/> Occident and
                I have to beg that you will receive this<lb/> as official and consider it as the
                communication of the<lb/> Committee.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The statement we have to put forth will occupy<lb/> many pages of your
                periodical&#44; therefore we do not/</p>

            <pb n="2"/>

            <p>conclusions&#44; but certainly think it will materially<lb/> affect the views
                    <del>that</del> which the editorial comments of the<lb/> Asmonean may have given
                you.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I send you my cordial greetings and best<lb/> wishes for your enjoyment of the
            approaching Festival</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Very faithfully Yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName role="author">Benjn. W. Hart</persName></p>
            <p>Address to me<lb/> Care of Ballin &#38; Sander</p>

        </body>
    </text>
